s-enduring-uk-us-ties/articleshow/132182502.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-04T19:07:31+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132182543,imgsize-120110.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Demanded $100,000 for our release': Pakistan gang rape victim names deputy PM Ishaq Dar's kin]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132179179.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A cryptocurrency dispute is now central to the investigation of an alleged kidnapping and gang rape of two foreign women in Pakistan. One victim claims Raza Dar, a relative of the deputy prime minister, demanded $100,000 for their release after they were held captive and sexually assaulted. Investigators are exploring if Dar lured the women to Pakistan for a $1.5 million crypto deal, staging the abduction to appear genuine.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/demanded-100000-for-our-release-pakistan-gang-rape-victim-names-deputy-pm-ishaq-dars-kin/articleshow/132179179.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/demanded-100000-for-our-release-pakistan-gang-rape-victim-names-deputy-pm-ishaq-dars-kin/articleshow/132179179.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-04T16:33:16+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132180067,imgsize-108833.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‎Which countries allow foreigners to adopt children? Here's what the rules look like]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132178449.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[International adoption landscapes are shifting dramatically. Many nations now prioritize domestic placements, making cross-border adoptions a last resort. Countries like China have ended programs for non-relatives, while others, including India and Vietnam, maintain regulated systems. Prospective parents face longer waits and stricter scrutiny globally as rules tighten, reflecting a growing emphasis on child welfare within their home countries]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/which-countries-allow-foreigners-to-adopt-children-heres-what-the-rules-look-like/articleshow/132178449.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/which-countries-allow-foreigners-to-adopt-children-heres-what-the-rules-look-like/articleshow/132178449.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-04T15:50:33+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132178497,imgsize-2397309.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[This toad exists only in Canada—and scientists have finally discovered why]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132178677.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Scientists have discovered a genetically unique western toad population exclusively in Canada, a finding that could be more distinctively Canadian than native wildlife. This rare group, found in the Rockies, highlights the importance of conserving unique genetic diversity. The research reveals deeper genetic divisions within the species, emphasizing that even common animals can harbor irreplaceable natural heritage.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/this-toad-exists-only-in-canadaand-scientists-have-finally-discovered-why/articleshow/132178677.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/this-toad-exists-only-in-canadaand-scientists-have-finally-discovered-why/articleshow/132178677.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-04T15:18:33+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132178733,imgsize-162221.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Up to 3,000 dead would be okay': Iran braces for mass casualties at Khamenei's funeral; report]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132178730.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/up-to-3000-dead-would-be-okay-iran-braces-for-mass-casualties-at-khameneis-funeral-report/articleshow/132178730.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/up-to-3000-dead-would-be-okay-iran-braces-for-mass-casualties-at-khameneis-funeral-report/articleshow/132178730.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-04T15:22:58+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132179006,imgsize-230360.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[China's Xi Jinping promotes two PLA generals after anti-corruption purge thins top military ranks]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132178740.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[China's leader, Xi Jinping, has made notable advancements by promoting two military officials to generals, marking a pivotal change in the People's Liberation Army's hierarchy. Following rigorous anti-corruption efforts that reshaped the leadership structure, these promotions are essential for restoring loyalty and filling key positions within the Central Military Commission, setting the stage for a comprehensive reorganization prior to the forthcoming Communist Party congress.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/chinas-xi-jinping-promotes-two-pla-generals-after-anti-corruption-purge-thins-top-military-ranks/articleshow/132178740.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/china/chinas-xi-jinping-promotes-two-pla-generals-after-anti-corruption-purge-thins-top-military-ranks/articleshow/132178740.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-04T15:21:48+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132178954,imgsize-77716.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UK parents urged not to share children's photos publicly over AI-enabled child abuse risks]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132178667.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/think-before-you-post-uk-parents-urged-to-stop-sharing-kids-photos-publicly-amid-ai-abuse-risks/articleshow/132178667.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/think-before-you-post-uk-parents-urged-to-stop-sharing-kids-photos-publicly-amid-ai-abuse-risks/articleshow/132178667.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-04T15:18:28+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132178713,imgsize-79002.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ethiopia's Danakil Depression looks like another planet and scientists know exactly why]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132177487.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/ethiopias-danakil-depress